assylias.jbloomberg

Class SingleRequestResult<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • assylias.jbloomberg.AbstractRequestResult
      • assylias.jbloomberg.SingleRequestResult<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestResult

    public class SingleRequestResult<T>
extends AbstractRequestResult
    A class that represents the result returned by a Bloomberg intraday request (which only accept one security). This implementation uses guava's MultiMap: each key (date) contains one or more entries (typically, several ticks can happen at the same millisecond).
    The values in the map are either Bar objects or Tick objects.
    This class is thread safe by being synchronized. That would not scale very well under high contention but that is an unlikely use case.
